# 🍽️ Nom Nom — Microfrontend Food Ordering App

A microfrontend application built with **Vite**, **Module Federation**, and **Tailwind CSS v4**. Three independently deployable apps work together to deliver a seamless food ordering experience.

---

## Architecture

```
Micro-Front/
└── apps/
    ├── container/   # Host app — composes menu and cart (port 3000)
    ├── menu/        # Remote — renders food cards (port 3001)
    └── order/       # Remote — manages the shopping cart (port 3002)
```

Each app is fully independent with its own `package.json`, `vite.config.js`, and Tailwind setup. The container loads `menu` and `order` at runtime via **Module Federation**.

---

## Tech Stack

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/) | Build tool and dev server |
| [@originjs/vite-plugin-federation](https://github.com/originjs/vite-plugin-federation) | Module Federation for microfrontends |
| [Tailwind CSS v4](https://tailwindcss.com/) | Utility-first styling |
| PostCSS + Autoprefixer | CSS processing |

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- npm 9+

### Install dependencies in each app

```bash
cd apps/menu && npm install
cd apps/order && npm install
cd apps/container && npm install
```

### Run (always build before preview — Module Federation requires it)

```bash
# Terminal 1
cd apps/menu && npm run build && npm run preview

# Terminal 2
cd apps/order && npm run build && npm run preview

# Terminal 3 — container last, depends on menu and order being up
cd apps/container && npm run build && npm run preview
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

> ⚠️ Always start `menu` and `order` before `container`. The container fetches their `remoteEntry.js` at runtime.

---

## Tailwind CSS v4 Setup

This project uses **Tailwind v4**, which changed how content scanning works. The `content` array in `tailwind.config.js` is no longer used. Instead, source paths are declared directly in `styles.css` using `@source`:

```css
/* styles.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@source "./menu.js";   /* or whichever files contain Tailwind classes */
```

The container also scans the remote apps' source files:

```css
/* container/src/styles.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@source "../../menu/src/**/*.js";
@source "../../order/src/**/*.js";
```

---

## Module Federation Config

### Container (host)
```js
federation({
  name: 'container',
  remotes: {
    menu: 'http://localhost:3001/assets/remoteEntry.js',
    order: 'http://localhost:3002/assets/remoteEntry.js',
  },
})
```

### Menu (remote)
```js
federation({
  name: 'menu',
  filename: 'remoteEntry.js',
  exposes: { './menu': './src/menu.js' },
})
```

### Order (remote)
```js
federation({
  name: 'order',
  filename: 'remoteEntry.js',
  exposes: { './order': './src/order.js' },
})
```

---

## Accessibility

This app is built with Lighthouse and WCAG AA compliance in mind:

- Semantic HTML — `<main>`, `<header>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<ul>/<li>`
- `lang="en"` on `<html>` for screen reader language detection
- `aria-label` on all interactive elements and landmarks
- `aria-live="polite"` on the cart list so screen readers announce updates
- Visible focus rings on all buttons (`focus:ring-2`)
- Sufficient color contrast (amber on white meets AA ratio)
- Descriptive `<meta name="description">` for SEO
- `defer` on scripts to prevent layout blocking

---

## Common Issues

**Styles not showing after a change?**
You must rebuild the specific app that changed, then rebuild the container:
```bash
cd apps/menu && npm run build && npm run preview
cd apps/container && npm run build && npm run preview
```

**CSS file is empty or missing classes?**
Make sure `styles.css` uses the v4 syntax and `@source` points to the right files:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@source "./yourfile.js";
```

**Port conflicts?**
Each app's `vite.config.js` needs a `preview` block in addition to `server`:
```js
preview: {
  host: 'localhost',
  port: 3001, // match the expected port
  strictPort: true,
}
```